// ============================================
// README.md
// ============================================
/*
# C REO Agency - Backend API

Comprehensive backend API for the C REO Marketing Agency website with full CRUD operations, authentication, file uploads, and email notifications.

## Features

✅ Contact Form Management
✅ Newsletter Subscription System
✅ Portfolio Management with Image & PDF Uploads
✅ Testimonials Management
✅ Service Inquiry Tracking
✅ Admin Authentication & Authorization
✅ Analytics Tracking
✅ Email Notifications (Nodemailer)
✅ File Upload (Images & PDFs)
✅ Data Export (CSV)
✅ RESTful API Design
✅ MongoDB Database
✅ JWT Authentication
✅ Role-Based Access Control

## Installation

1. Clone the repository
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

3. Create .env file (copy from .env.example):
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   ```

4. Configure your environment variables in .env

5. Start MongoDB (if running locally):
   ```bash
   mongod
   ```

6. Run the server:
   ```bash
   # Development mode with auto-reload
   npm run dev

   # Production mode
   npm start
   ```

## API Endpoints

### Public Endpoints

#### Contact Form
- POST `/api/contact` - Submit contact form
  ```json
  {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "phone": "+1234567890",
    "company": "Tech Corp",
    "service": "Social Media Marketing",
    "message": "I need help with social media",
    "budget": "$10000-$25000"
  }
  ```

#### Newsletter
- POST `/api/newsletter/subscribe` - Subscribe to newsletter
  ```json
  {
    "email": "subscriber@example.com",
    "name": "Jane Doe"
  }
  ```

#### Portfolio
- GET `/api/portfolio` - Get all portfolio items (paginated)
  - Query params: `?page=1&limit=12&category=Branding`
- GET `/api/portfolio/featured` - Get featured portfolio items
- GET `/api/portfolio/:id` - Get single portfolio item

#### Testimonials
- GET `/api/testimonials` - Get approved testimonials
  - Query params: `?featured=true`

#### Service Inquiry
- POST `/api/service-inquiry` - Submit service inquiry
  ```json
  {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "phone": "+1234567890",
    "service": "Photography",
    "projectDetails": "Need product photography",
    "timeline": "1-3 months",
    "budget": "$5000-$10000",
    "referralSource": "Google"
  }
  ```

#### Analytics
- POST `/api/analytics/track` - Track user events
  ```json
  {
    "event": "page_view",
    "page": "/services",
    "sessionId": "session-123",
    "metadata": { "duration": 45 }
  }
  ```

### Admin Authentication

#### Login
- POST `/api/admin/login` - Admin login
  ```json
  {
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "your-password"
  }
  ```
  Returns JWT token for authenticated requests

#### Setup (Run Once)
- POST `/api/admin/setup` - Create first admin account
  ```json
  {
    "username": "admin",
    "email": "admin@creoagency.com",
    "password": "secure-password"
  }
  ```

### Admin Protected Endpoints
(Require Authorization header: `Bearer <token>`)

#### Contacts Management
- GET `/api/admin/contacts` - Get all contacts (paginated)
- PATCH `/api/admin/contacts/:id` - Update contact status
- GET `/api/admin/contacts/export` - Export contacts to CSV

#### Portfolio Management
- POST `/api/admin/portfolio` - Create portfolio item (multipart/form-data)
- PUT `/api/admin/portfolio/:id` - Update portfolio item
- DELETE `/api/admin/portfolio/:id` - Delete portfolio item

#### Testimonials Management
- GET `/api/admin/testimonials` - Get all testimonials
- POST `/api/admin/testimonials` - Create testimonial
- PUT `/api/admin/testimonials/:id` - Update testimonial
- DELETE `/api/admin/testimonials/:id` - Delete testimonial

#### Service Inquiries
- GET `/api/admin/inquiries` - Get all service inquiries
- PATCH `/api/admin/inquiries/:id` - Update inquiry status

#### Newsletter Management
- GET `/api/admin/newsletter` - Get all subscribers
- POST `/api/admin/newsletter/send` - Send newsletter to all subscribers
  ```json
  {
    "subject": "Monthly Newsletter",
    "htmlContent": "<h1>Hello!</h1><p>Newsletter content...</p>"
  }
  ```

#### Analytics
- GET `/api/admin/analytics/dashboard` - Get dashboard statistics
- GET `/api/admin/analytics/events` - Get tracked events

## Database Models

### Contact
- name, email, phone, company, service, message, budget, status, source, createdAt

### Newsletter
- email, name, isActive, subscribedAt

### Portfolio
- title, description, category, client, industry, results[], images[], pdfFile, link, featured, publishedAt

### Testimonial
- name, role, company, content, rating, image, featured, isApproved, createdAt

### ServiceInquiry
- name, email, phone, service, projectDetails, timeline, budget, referralSource, status

### Admin
- username, email, password (hashed), role, isActive, lastLogin

### Analytics
- event, page, userId, sessionId, metadata, ipAddress, userAgent, timestamp

## Authentication & Authorization

### Roles
- **admin**: Full access to all endpoints
- **editor**: Can manage content (portfolio, testimonials, contacts)
- **viewer**: Read-only access to data

### JWT Token
- Expires in 24 hours
- Include in Authorization header: `Bearer <token>`

## File Uploads

### Supported Files
- **Images**: JPEG, JPG, PNG, GIF, WEBP (max 10MB)
- **PDFs**: PDF documents (max 10MB)

### Upload Endpoints
- Portfolio creation/update supports multiple images and one PDF
- Files stored in `/uploads/images` and `/uploads/pdfs`

## Email Configuration

### Gmail Setup
1. Enable 2-factor authentication in Gmail
2. Generate app-specific password
3. Use in SMTP_PASS environment variable

### Email Types
- Contact form confirmation
- Admin notifications
- Newsletter welcome
- Newsletter broadcasts

## Security Features

✅ Password hashing (bcrypt)
✅ JWT token authentication
✅ Role-based access control
✅ Input validation
✅ SQL injection protection (MongoDB)
✅ File type validation
✅ Rate limiting ready
✅ CORS configuration

## Development

### Running in Development Mode
```bash
npm run dev
```

### Testing Endpoints
Use Postman, Insomnia, or curl:

```bash
# Test health check
curl http://localhost:5000/api/health

# Submit contact form
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/contact \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name":"Test","email":"test@example.com","message":"Hello"}'

# Admin login
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"username":"admin","password":"your-password"}'
```

## Production Deployment

### Environment Variables
- Set NODE_ENV=production
- Use strong JWT_SECRET
- Configure production MongoDB URI
- Set up proper SMTP credentials
- Configure CORS for your domain

### Recommended Services
- **Hosting**: Heroku, DigitalOcean, AWS, Railway
- **Database**: MongoDB Atlas (free tier available)
- **Email**: SendGrid, Mailgun, AWS SES
- **File Storage**: AWS S3, Cloudinary (for production file uploads)

### Deployment Checklist
- [ ] Set all environment variables
- [ ] Create admin account
- [ ] Test email configuration
- [ ] Configure CORS for frontend domain
- [ ] Set up file upload directory or cloud storage
- [ ] Enable HTTPS
- [ ] Set up monitoring and logging
- [ ] Configure backup strategy

## Folder Structure
```
creo-agency-backend/
├── server.js              # Main application file
├── package.json           # Dependencies
├── .env                   # Environment variables (create this)
├── .env.example          # Environment template
├── .gitignore            # Git ignore file
├── uploads/              # File uploads directory
│   ├── images/          # Portfolio images
│   └── pdfs/            # Portfolio PDFs
└── README.md            # This file
```

## Support

For issues or questions:
- Email: dev@creoagency.com
- Documentation: API documentation available at /api/docs (if implemented)

## License

MIT License - See LICENSE file for details
*/

